\c 5  
\p
\v 1 Run ye to and fro through the streets of Jerusalem, and see now, and know, and seek in the broad places thereof, if ye can find a man, if there be \add any\add* that executeth judgment, that seeketh the truth; and I will pardon it. 
\v 2 And though they say, The \sc Lord\sc* liveth; surely they swear falsely. 
\v 3 O \sc Lord\sc*, \add are\add* not thine eyes upon the truth? thou hast stricken them, but they have not grieved; thou hast consumed them, \add but\add* they have refused to receive correction: they have made their faces harder than a rock; they have refused to return. 
\v 4 Therefore I said, Surely these \add are\add* poor; they are foolish: for they know not the way of the \sc Lord\sc*, \add nor\add* the judgment of their God. 
\v 5 I will get me unto the great men, and will speak unto them; for they have known the way of the \sc Lord\sc*, \add and\add* the judgment of their God: but these have altogether broken the yoke, \add and\add* burst the bonds. 
\v 6 Wherefore a lion out of the forest shall slay them, \add and\add* a wolf of the evenings shall spoil them, a leopard shall watch over their cities: every one that goeth out thence shall be torn in pieces: because their transgressions are many, \add and\add* their backslidings are increased. 
\v 7 How shall I pardon thee for this? thy children have forsaken me, and sworn by \add them that are\add* no gods: when I had fed them to the full, they then committed adultery, and assembled themselves by troops \add in\add* the harlots’ houses. 
\v 8 They were \add as\add* fed horses in the morning: every one neighed after his neighbour’s wife. 
\v 9 Shall I not visit for these \add things?\add* saith the \sc Lord\sc*: and shall not my soul be avenged on such a nation as this? 
\p
\v 10 Go ye up upon her walls, and destroy; but make not a full end: take away her battlements; for they \add are\add* not the \sc Lord’s\sc*. 
\v 11 For the house of Israel and the house of Judah have dealt very treacherously against me, saith the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 12 They have belied the \sc Lord\sc*, and said, \add It is\add* not he; neither shall evil come upon us; neither shall we see sword nor famine: 
\v 13 and the prophets shall become wind, and the word \add is\add* not in them: thus shall it be done unto them. 
\v 14 Wherefore thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* God of hosts, Because ye speak this word, behold, I will make my words in thy mouth fire, and this people wood, and it shall devour them. 
\v 15 Lo, I will bring a nation upon you from far, O house of Israel, saith the \sc Lord\sc*: it \add is\add* a mighty nation, it \add is\add* an ancient nation, a nation whose language thou knowest not, neither understandest what they say. 
\v 16 Their quiver \add is\add* as an open sepulchre, they \add are\add* all mighty \add men\add*. 
\v 17 And they shall eat up thine harvest, and thy bread, \add which\add* thy sons and thy daughters should eat: they shall eat up thy flocks and thine herds: they shall eat up thy vines and thy fig trees: they shall impoverish thy fenced cities, wherein thou trustedst, with the sword. 
\v 18 Nevertheless in those days, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, I will not make a full end with you. 
\p
\v 19 And it shall come to pass, when ye shall say, Wherefore doth the \sc Lord\sc* our God all these \add things\add* unto us? then shalt thou answer them, Like as ye have forsaken me, and served strange gods in your land, so shall ye serve strangers in a land \add that is\add* not yours. 
\v 20 Declare this in the house of Jacob, and publish it in Judah, saying, 
\v 21 Hear now this, O foolish people, and without understanding; which have eyes, and see not; which have ears, and hear not: 
\v 22 fear ye not me? saith the \sc Lord\sc*: will ye not tremble at my presence, which have placed the sand \add for\add* the bound of the sea \add by\add* a perpetual decree, that it cannot pass it: and though the waves thereof toss themselves, yet can they not prevail; though they roar, yet can they not pass over it? 
\v 23 But this people hath a revolting and a rebellious heart; they are revolted and gone. 
\v 24 Neither say they in their heart, Let us now fear the \sc Lord\sc* our God, that giveth rain, both the former and the latter, in his season: he reserveth unto us the appointed weeks of the harvest. 
\v 25 Your iniquities have turned away these \add things\add*, and your sins have withholden good \add things\add* from you. 
\v 26 For among my people are found wicked \add men:\add* they lay wait, as he that setteth snares; they set a trap, they catch men. 
\v 27 As a cage \add is\add* full \add of\add* birds, so \add are\add* their houses full \add of\add* deceit: therefore they are become great, and waxen rich. 
\v 28 They are waxen fat, they shine: yea, they overpass the deeds of the wicked: they judge not the cause, the cause of the fatherless, yet they prosper; and the right of the needy do they not judge. 
\v 29 Shall I not visit for these \add things?\add* saith the \sc Lord\sc*: shall not my soul be avenged on such a nation as this? 
\p
\v 30 A wonderful and horrible thing is committed in the land; 
\v 31 the prophets prophesy falsely, and the priests bear rule by their means; and my people love \add to have it\add* so: and what will ye do in the end thereof? 
\c 6  
\p
\v 1 O ye children of Benjamin, gather yourselves to flee out of the midst of Jerusalem, and blow the trumpet in Tekoa, and set up a sign of fire in Beth-haccerem: for evil appeareth out of the north, and great destruction. 
\v 2 I have likened the daughter of Zion \add to\add* a comely and delicate \add woman\add*. 
\v 3 The shepherds with their flocks shall come unto her; they shall pitch \add their\add* tents against her round about; they shall feed every one \add in\add* his place. 
\v 4 Prepare ye war against her; arise, and let us go up at noon. Woe unto us! for the day goeth away, for the shadows of the evening are stretched out. 
\v 5 Arise, and let us go by night, and let us destroy her palaces. 
\v 6 For thus hath the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts said, Hew ye down trees, and cast a mount against Jerusalem: this is the city to be visited; she \add is\add* wholly oppression in the midst of her. 
\v 7 As a fountain casteth out her waters, so she casteth out her wickedness: violence and spoil is heard in her; before me continually \add is\add* grief and wounds. 
\v 8 Be thou instructed, O Jerusalem, lest my soul depart from thee; lest I make thee desolate, a land not inhabited. 
\p
\v 9 Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, They shall throughly glean the remnant of Israel as a vine: turn back thine hand as a grapegatherer into the baskets. 
\v 10 To whom shall I speak, and give warning, that they may hear? behold, their ear \add is\add* uncircumcised, and they cannot hearken: behold, the word of the \sc Lord\sc* is unto them a reproach; they have no delight in it. 
\v 11 Therefore I am full \add of\add* the fury of the \sc Lord\sc*; I am weary with holding in: I \add will\add* pour \add it\add* out upon the children abroad, and upon the assembly of young men together: for even the husband with the wife shall be taken, the aged with \add him that is\add* full of days. 
\v 12 And their houses shall be turned unto others, \add with their\add* fields and wives together: for I will stretch out my hand upon the inhabitants of the land, saith the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 13 For from the least of them even unto the greatest of them every one \add is\add* given to covetousness; and from the prophet even unto the priest every one dealeth falsely. 
\v 14 They have healed also the hurt of \add the daughter of\add* my people slightly, saying, Peace, peace; when \add there is\add* no peace. 
\v 15 Were they ashamed when they had committed abomination? nay, they were not at all ashamed, neither could they blush: therefore they shall fall among them that fall: at the time \add that\add* I visit them they shall be cast down, saith the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 16 Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*, Stand ye in the ways, and see, and ask for the old paths, where \add is\add* the good way, and walk therein, and ye shall find rest for your souls. But they said, We will not walk \add therein\add*. 
