\c 26  
\p
\v 1 In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah came this word from the \sc Lord\sc*, saying, 
\v 2 Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Stand in the court of the \sc Lord’s\sc* house, and speak unto all the cities of Judah, which come to worship \add in\add* the \sc Lord’s\sc* house, all the words that I command thee to speak unto them; diminish not a word: 
\v 3 if so be they will hearken, and turn every man from his evil way, that I may repent me of the evil, which I purpose to do unto them because of the evil of their doings. 
\v 4 And thou shalt say unto them, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; If ye will not hearken to me, to walk in my law, which I have set before you, 
\v 5 to hearken to the words of my servants the prophets, whom I sent unto you, both rising up early, and sending \add them\add*, but ye have not hearkened; 
\v 6 then will I make this house like Shiloh, and will make this city a curse to all the nations of the earth. 
\p
\v 7 So the priests and the prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah speaking these words in the house of the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 8 Now it came to pass, when Jeremiah had made an end of speaking all that the \sc Lord\sc* had commanded \add him\add* to speak unto all the people, that the priests and the prophets and all the people took him, saying, Thou shalt surely die. 
\v 9 Why hast thou prophesied in the name of the \sc Lord\sc*, saying, This house shall be like Shiloh, and this city shall be desolate without an inhabitant? And all the people were gathered against Jeremiah in the house of the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 10 When the princes of Judah heard these things, then they came up from the king’s house \add unto\add* the house of the \sc Lord\sc*, and sat down in the entry of the new gate of the \sc Lord’s\sc* \add house\add*. 
\v 11 Then spake the priests and the prophets unto the princes and to all the people, saying, This man \add is\add* worthy to die; for he hath prophesied against this city, as ye have heard with your ears. 
\v 12 Then spake Jeremiah unto all the princes and to all the people, saying, The \sc Lord\sc* sent me to prophesy against this house and against this city all the words that ye have heard. 
\v 13 Therefore now amend your ways and your doings, and obey the voice of the \sc Lord\sc* your God; and the \sc Lord\sc* will repent him of the evil that he hath pronounced against you. 
\v 14 As for me, behold, I \add am\add* in your hand: do with me as seemeth good and meet unto you. 
\v 15 But know ye for certain, that if ye put me to death, ye shall surely bring innocent blood upon yourselves, and upon this city, and upon the inhabitants thereof: for of a truth the \sc Lord\sc* hath sent me unto you to speak all these words in your ears. 
\p
\v 16 Then said the princes and all the people unto the priests and to the prophets; This man \add is\add* not worthy to die: for he hath spoken to us in the name of the \sc Lord\sc* our God. 
\v 17 Then rose up certain of the elders of the land, and spake to all the assembly of the people, saying, 
\v 18 Micah the Morasthite prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and spake to all the people of Judah, saying, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts; 
\q1 Zion shall be plowed \add like\add* a field, 
\q1 And Jerusalem shall become heaps, 
\q1 And the mountain of the house as the high places of a forest. 
\p
\v 19 Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah put him at all to death? did he not fear the \sc Lord\sc*, and besought the \sc Lord\sc*, and the \sc Lord\sc* repented him of the evil which he had pronounced against them? Thus \add might\add* we procure great evil against our souls. 
\v 20 And there was also a man that prophesied in the name of the \sc Lord\sc*, Urijah the son of Shemaiah of Kirjath-jearim, who prophesied against this city and against this land according to all the words of Jeremiah: 
\v 21 and when Jehoiakim the king, with all his mighty \add men\add*, and all the princes, heard his words, the king sought to put him to death: but when Urijah heard \add it\add*, he was afraid, and fled, and went \add into\add* Egypt; 
\v 22 and Jehoiakim the king sent men \add into\add* Egypt, \add namely\add*, Elnathan the son of Achbor, and \add certain\add* men with him into Egypt. 
\v 23 And they fet forth Urijah out of Egypt, and brought him unto Jehoiakim the king; who slew him with the sword, and cast his dead body into the graves of the common people. 
\v 24 Nevertheless the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah, that \add they\add* should not give him into the hand of the people to put him to death. 
\c 27  
\p
\v 1 In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah came this word unto Jeremiah from the \sc Lord\sc*, saying, 
\v 2 Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* to me; Make thee bonds and yokes, and put them upon thy neck, 
\v 3 and send them to the king of Edom, and to the king of Moab, and to the king of the Ammonites, and to the king of Tyrus, and to the king of Zidon, by the hand of the messengers which come \add to\add* Jerusalem unto Zedekiah king of Judah; 
\v 4 and command them to say unto their masters, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel; Thus shall ye say unto your masters; 
\v 5 I have made the earth, the man and the beast that \add are\add* upon the ground, by my great power and by my outstretched arm, and have given it unto whom it seemed meet unto me. 
\v 6 And now have I given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, my servant; and the beasts of the field have I given him also to serve him. 
\v 7 And all nations shall serve him, and his son, and his son’s son, until the very time of his land come: and \add then\add* many nations and great kings shall serve themselves of him. 
\v 8 And it shall come to pass, \add that\add* the nation and kingdom which will not serve the same Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, and that will not put their neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, that nation will I punish, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, with the sword, and with the famine, and with the pestilence, until I have consumed them by his hand. 
\v 9 Therefore hearken not ye to your prophets, nor to your diviners, nor to your dreamers, nor to your enchanters, nor to your sorcerers, which speak unto you, saying, Ye shall not serve the king of Babylon: 
\v 10 for they prophesy a lie unto you, to remove you far from your land; and \add that\add* I should drive you out, and ye should perish. 
\v 11 But the nations that bring their neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and serve him, those will I let remain still in their own land, saith the \sc Lord\sc*; and they shall till it, and dwell therein. 
\p
\v 12 I spake also to Zedekiah king of Judah according to all these words, saying, Bring your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and serve him and his people, and live. 
\v 13 Why will ye die, thou and thy people, by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence, as the \sc Lord\sc* hath spoken against the nation that will not serve the king of Babylon? 
\v 14 Therefore hearken not unto the words of the prophets that speak unto you, saying, Ye shall not serve the king of Babylon: for they prophesy a lie unto you. 
\v 15 For I have not sent them, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, yet they prophesy a lie in my name; that I might drive you out, and that ye might perish, ye, and the prophets that prophesy unto you. 
\v 16 Also I spake to the priests and to all this people, saying, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Hearken not to the words of your prophets that prophesy unto you, saying, Behold, the vessels of the \sc Lord’s\sc* house \add shall\add* now shortly be brought again from Babylon: for they prophesy a lie unto you. 
\v 17 Hearken not unto them; serve the king of Babylon, and live: wherefore should this city be laid waste? 
\v 18 But if they \add be\add* prophets, and if the word of the \sc Lord\sc* be with them, let them now make intercession to the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, that the vessels which are left in the house of the \sc Lord\sc*, and \add in\add* the house of the king of Judah, and at Jerusalem, go not to Babylon. 
\v 19 For thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts concerning the pillars, and concerning the sea, and concerning the bases, and concerning the residue of the vessels that remain in this city, 
\v 20 which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took not, when he carried away captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah from Jerusalem to Babylon, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem; 
\v 21 yea, thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning the vessels that remain \add in\add* the house of the \sc Lord\sc*, and \add in\add* the house of the king of Judah and of Jerusalem; 
\v 22 they shall be carried to Babylon, and there shall they be until the day that I visit them, saith the \sc Lord\sc*; then will I bring them up, and restore them to this place. 
\c 28  
\p
\v 1 And it came to pass the same year, in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the fourth year, \add and\add* in the fifth month, \add that\add* Hananiah the son of Azur the prophet, which \add was\add* of Gibeon, spake unto me in the house of the \sc Lord\sc*, in the presence of the priests and of all the people, saying, 
\v 2 Thus speaketh the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel, saying, I have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon. 
\v 3 Within two full years \add will\add* I bring again into this place all the vessels of the \sc Lord’s\sc* house, that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took away from this place, and carried them \add to\add* Babylon: 
\v 4 and I \add will\add* bring again to this place Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah, with all the captives of Judah, that went into Babylon, saith the \sc Lord\sc*: for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon. 
\v 5 Then the prophet Jeremiah said unto the prophet Hananiah in the presence of the priests, and in the presence of all the people that stood in the house of the \sc Lord\sc*, 
\v 6 even the prophet Jeremiah said, Amen: the \sc Lord\sc* do so: the \sc Lord\sc* perform thy words which thou hast prophesied, to bring again the vessels of the \sc Lord’s\sc* house, and all that is carried away captive, from Babylon into this place. 
\v 7 Nevertheless hear thou now this word that I speak in thine ears, and in the ears of all the people. 
\v 8 The prophets that have been before me and before thee of old prophesied both against many countries, and against great kingdoms, of war, and of evil, and of pestilence. 
\v 9 The prophet which prophesieth of peace, when the word of the prophet shall come to pass, \add then\add* shall the prophet be known, that the \sc Lord\sc* hath truly sent him. 
\v 10 Then Hananiah the prophet took the yoke from off the prophet Jeremiah’s neck, and brake it. 
\v 11 And Hananiah spake in the presence of all the people, saying, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Even so will I break the yoke of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon from the neck of all nations within the space of two full years. And the prophet Jeremiah went his way. 
\p
\v 12 Then the word of the \sc Lord\sc* came unto Jeremiah \add the prophet\add*, after that Hananiah the prophet had broken the yoke from off the neck of the prophet Jeremiah, saying, 
\v 13 Go and tell Hananiah, saying, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Thou hast broken the yokes of wood; but thou shalt make for them yokes of iron. 
\v 14 For thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel; I have put a yoke of iron upon the neck of all these nations, that \add they\add* may serve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon; and they shall serve him: and I have given him the beasts of the field also. 
\v 15 Then said the prophet Jeremiah unto Hananiah the prophet, Hear now, Hananiah; The \sc Lord\sc* hath not sent thee; but thou makest this people to trust in a lie. 
\v 16 Therefore thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Behold, I will cast thee from off the face of the earth: \add this\add* year thou \add shalt\add* die, because thou hast taught rebellion against the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 17 So Hananiah the prophet died the same year in the seventh month. 
\c 29  
\p
\v 1 Now these \add are\add* the words of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent from Jerusalem unto the residue of the elders which were carried away captives, and to the priests, and to the prophets, and to all the people whom Nebuchadnezzar had carried away captive from Jerusalem to Babylon; 
\v 2 (after that Jeconiah the king, and the queen, and the eunuchs, the princes of Judah and Jerusalem, and the carpenters, and the smiths, were departed from Jerusalem;) 
\v 3 by the hand of Elasah the son of Shaphan, and Gemariah the son of Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent unto Babylon to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, saying, 
\p
\v 4 Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel, unto all that are carried away captives, whom I have caused to be carried away from Jerusalem unto Babylon; 
\v 5 Build ye houses, and dwell \add in them;\add* and plant gardens, and eat the fruit of them; 
\v 6 take ye wives, and beget sons and daughters; and take wives for your sons, and give your daughters to husbands, that they may bear sons and daughters; that ye may be increased there, and not diminished. 
\v 7 And seek the peace of the city whither I have caused you to be carried away captives, and pray unto the \sc Lord\sc* for it: for in the peace thereof shall ye have peace. 
\v 8 For thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel; Let not your prophets and your diviners, that \add be\add* in the midst of you, deceive you, neither hearken to your dreams which ye cause to be dreamed. 
\v 9 For they prophesy falsely unto you in my name: I have not sent them, saith the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 10 For thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*, That after seventy years be accomplished at Babylon I will visit you, and perform my good word towards you, in causing you to return to this place. 
\v 11 For I know the thoughts that I think towards you, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, thoughts of peace, and not of evil, to give you an expected end. 
\v 12 Then shall ye call upon me, and ye shall go and pray unto me, and I will hearken unto you. 
\v 13 And ye shall seek me, and find \add me\add*, when ye shall search for me with all your heart. 
\v 14 And I will be found of you, saith the \sc Lord\sc*: and I will turn away your captivity, and I will gather you from all the nations, and from all the places whither I have driven you, saith the \sc Lord\sc*; and I will bring you again into the place whence I caused you to be carried away captive. 
\p
\v 15 Because ye have said, The \sc Lord\sc* hath raised us up prophets in Babylon; 
\v 16  \add Know\add* that thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of the king that sitteth upon the throne of David, and of all the people that dwelleth in this city, \add and of\add* your brethren that are not gone forth with you into captivity; 
\v 17 thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts; Behold, I will send upon them the sword, the famine, and the pestilence, and will make them like vile figs, that cannot be eaten, they are so evil. 
\v 18 And I will persecute them with the sword, with the famine, and with the pestilence, and will deliver them to be removed to all the kingdoms of the earth, to be a curse, and an astonishment, and a hissing, and a reproach, among all the nations whither I have driven them: 
\v 19 because they have not hearkened to my words, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, which I sent unto them by my servants the prophets, rising up early and sending \add them;\add* but ye would not hear, saith the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\v 20 Hear ye therefore the word of the \sc Lord\sc*, all \add ye of\add* the captivity, whom I have sent from Jerusalem to Babylon: 
\v 21 thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel, of Ahab the son of Kolaiah, and of Zedekiah, the son of Maaseiah, which prophesy a lie unto you in my name; Behold, I will deliver them into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon; and he shall slay them before your eyes; 
\v 22 and of them shall be taken up a curse by all the captivity of Judah which \add are\add* in Babylon, saying, The \sc Lord\sc* make thee like Zedekiah and like Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire; 
\v 23 because they have committed villany in Israel, and have committed adultery with their neighbours’ wives, and have spoken lying words in my name, which I have not commanded them; even I know, and \add am\add* a witness, saith the \sc Lord\sc*. 
\p
\v 24  \add Thus\add* shalt thou also speak to Shemaiah the Nehelamite, saying, 
\v 25 Thus speaketh the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel, saying, Because thou hast sent letters in thy name unto all the people that \add are\add* at Jerusalem, and to Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah the priest, and to all the priests, saying, 
\v 26 The \sc Lord\sc* hath made thee priest in the stead of Jehoiada the priest, that \add ye\add* should be officers in the house of the \sc Lord\sc*, for every man \add that is\add* mad, and maketh himself a prophet, that thou shouldest put him in prison, and in the stocks. 
\v 27 Now therefore why hast thou not reproved Jeremiah of Anathoth, which maketh himself a prophet to you? 
\v 28 For therefore he sent unto us \add in\add* Babylon, saying, This \add captivity is\add* long: build ye houses, and dwell \add in them;\add* and plant gardens, and eat the fruit of them. 
\v 29 And Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the ears of Jeremiah the prophet. 
\v 30 Then came the word of the \sc Lord\sc* unto Jeremiah, saying, 
\v 31 Send to all them of the captivity, saying, Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* concerning Shemaiah the Nehelamite; Because that Shemaiah hath prophesied unto you, and I sent him not, and he caused you to trust in a lie: 
\v 32 therefore thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Behold, I will punish Shemaiah the Nehelamite, and his seed: he shall not have a man to dwell among this people; neither shall he behold the good that I will do for my people, saith the \sc Lord\sc*; because he hath taught rebellion against the \sc Lord\sc*. 
