\v 3 that the \sc Lord\sc* thy God may shew us the way wherein we may walk, and the thing that we may do. 
\v 4 Then Jeremiah the prophet said unto them, I have heard \add you;\add* behold, I \add will\add* pray unto the \sc Lord\sc* your God according to your words; and it shall come to pass, \add that\add* whatsoever thing the \sc Lord\sc* shall answer you, I will declare \add it\add* unto you; I will keep nothing back from you. 
\v 5 Then they said to Jeremiah, The \sc Lord\sc* be a true and faithful witness between us, if we do not even according to all things \add for\add* the which the \sc Lord\sc* thy God shall send thee to us. 
\v 6 Whether \add it be\add* good, or whether \add it be\add* evil, we will obey the voice of the \sc Lord\sc* our God, to whom we send thee; that it may be well with us, when we obey the voice of the \sc Lord\sc* our God. 
\p
\v 7 And it came to pass after ten days, that the word of the \sc Lord\sc* came unto Jeremiah. 
