\v 10 if ye will still abide in this land, then will I build you, and not pull \add you\add* down, and I will plant you, and not pluck \add you\add* up: for I repent me of the evil that I have done unto you. 
\v 11 Be not afraid of the king of Babylon, of whom ye \add are\add* afraid; be not afraid of him, saith the \sc Lord\sc*: for I \add am\add* with you to save you, and to deliver you from his hand. 
\v 12 And I will shew mercies unto you, that he may have mercy upon you, and cause you to return to your own land. 
\v 13 But if ye say, We will not dwell in this land, neither obey the voice of the \sc Lord\sc* your God, 
\v 14 saying, No; but we will go \add into\add* the land of Egypt, where we shall see no war, nor hear the sound of the trumpet, nor have hunger of bread; and there will we dwell: 
\v 15 and now therefore hear the word of the \sc Lord\sc*, ye remnant of Judah; Thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel; If ye wholly set your faces to enter \add into\add* Egypt, and go to sojourn there; 
\v 16 then it shall come to pass, \add that\add* the sword, which ye feared, shall overtake you there in the land of Egypt, and the famine, whereof ye were afraid, shall follow close after you there \add in\add* Egypt; and there ye shall die. 
\v 17 So shall it be with all the men that set their faces to go \add into\add* Egypt to sojourn there; they shall die by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence: and none of them shall remain or escape from the evil that I \add will\add* bring upon them. 
\v 18 For thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel; As mine anger and my fury hath been poured forth upon the inhabitants of Jerusalem; so shall my fury be poured forth upon you, when ye shall enter \add into\add* Egypt: and ye shall be an execration, and an astonishment, and a curse, and a reproach; and ye shall see this place no more. 
\v 19 The \sc Lord\sc* hath said concerning you, O ye remnant of Judah; Go ye not \add into\add* Egypt: know certainly that I have admonished you \add this\add* day. 
\v 20 For ye dissembled in your hearts, when ye sent me unto the \sc Lord\sc* your God, saying, Pray for us unto the \sc Lord\sc* our God; and according unto all that the \sc Lord\sc* our God shall say, so declare unto us, and we will do \add it\add*. 
\v 21 And \add now\add* I have \add this\add* day declared \add it\add* to you; but ye have not obeyed the voice of the \sc Lord\sc* your God, nor any \add thing\add* for the which he hath sent me unto you. 
\v 22 Now therefore know certainly that ye shall die by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence, in the place whither ye desire to go \add and\add* to sojourn. 
\c 43  
