\v 10 They are not humbled \add even\add* unto this day, neither have they feared, nor walked in my law, nor in my statutes, that I set before you and before your fathers. 
\p
\v 11 Therefore thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel; Behold, I will set my face against you for evil, and to cut off all Judah. 
\v 12 And I will take the remnant of Judah, that have set their faces to go \add into\add* the land of Egypt to sojourn there, and they shall all be consumed, \add and\add* fall in the land of Egypt; they shall \add even\add* be consumed by the sword, \add and\add* by the famine: they shall die, from the least even unto the greatest, by the sword and by the famine: and they shall be an execration, \add and\add* an astonishment, and a curse, and a reproach. 
\v 13 For I will punish them that dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have punished Jerusalem, by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence: 
\v 14 so that none of the remnant of Judah, which are gone into the land of Egypt to sojourn there, shall escape or remain, that \add they\add* should return \add into\add* the land of Judah, to the which they have a desire to return to dwell there: for none shall return but such as shall escape. 
\p
\v 15 Then all the men which knew that their wives had burnt incense unto other gods, and all the women that stood \add by\add*, a great multitude, even all the people that dwelt in the land of Egypt, in Pathros, answered Jeremiah, saying, 
\v 16  \add As for\add* the word that thou hast spoken unto us in the name of the \sc Lord\sc*, we will not hearken unto thee. 
\v 17 But we will certainly do whatsoever thing goeth forth out of our own mouth, to burn incense unto the queen of heaven, and to pour out drink offerings unto her, as we have done, we, and our fathers, our kings, and our princes, in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem: for \add then\add* had we plenty of victuals, and were well, and saw no evil. 
\v 18 But since we left off to burn incense to the queen of heaven, and to pour out drink offerings unto her, we have wanted all \add things\add*, and have been consumed by the sword and by the famine. 
\v 19 And when we burnt incense to the queen of heaven, and poured out drink offerings unto her, did we make her cakes to worship her, and pour out drink offerings unto her, without our men? 
\p
\v 20 Then Jeremiah said unto all the people, to the men, and to the women, and to all the people which had given him \add that\add* answer, saying, 
\v 21 The incense that ye burnt in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, ye, and your fathers, your kings, and your princes, and the people of the land, did not the \sc Lord\sc* remember them, and came it \add not\add* into his mind? 
\v 22 So that the \sc Lord\sc* could no longer bear, because of the evil of your doings, \add and\add* because of the abominations which ye have committed; therefore is your land a desolation, and an astonishment, and a curse, without an inhabitant, as \add at\add* this day. 
\v 23 Because you have burnt incense, and because ye have sinned against the \sc Lord\sc*, and have not obeyed the voice of the \sc Lord\sc*, nor walked in his law, nor in his statutes, nor in his testimonies; therefore this evil is happened unto you, as \add at\add* this day. 
\p
\v 24 Moreover Jeremiah said unto all the people, and to all the women, Hear the word of the \sc Lord\sc*, all Judah that \add are\add* in the land of Egypt: 
\v 25 thus saith the \sc Lord\sc* of hosts, the God of Israel, saying; Ye and your wives have both spoken with your mouths, and fulfilled with your hand, saying, We will surely perform our vows that we have vowed, to burn incense to the queen of heaven, and to pour out drink offerings unto her: ye will surely accomplish your vows, and surely perform your vows. 
\v 26 Therefore hear ye the word of the \sc Lord\sc*, all Judah that dwell in the land of Egypt; Behold, I have sworn by my great name, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, that my name shall no more be named in the mouth of any man of Judah in all the land of Egypt, saying, The Lord \sc God\sc* liveth. 
\v 27 Behold, I \add will\add* watch over them for evil, and not for good: and all the men of Judah that \add are\add* in the land of Egypt shall be consumed by the sword and by the famine, until there be an end of them. 
\v 28 Yet a small number that escape the sword shall return out of the land of Egypt \add into\add* the land of Judah, and all the remnant of Judah, that are gone into the land of Egypt to sojourn there, shall know whose words shall stand, mine, or theirs. 
\v 29 And this \add shall be\add* a sign unto you, saith the \sc Lord\sc*, that I will punish you in this place, that ye may know that my words shall surely stand against you for evil: 
\v 30 thus saith the \sc Lord\sc*; Behold, I \add will\add* give Pharaoh-hophra king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies, and into the hand of them that seek his life; as I gave Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, his enemy, and that sought his life. 
